String : is a non primitive data 

string are used to represent text or a group of characters together


String s = "hello";

h - 0
e - 1
l - 2
l - 3
o - 4

Note : a string is always enclosed  in b/w  double quotes

methods of string 

 length() : no of characters in a string
 
 toUpperCase() : converts the given string to upper case completely
 
 toLowerCase() :   converts the given string to lower case completely
 
 indexOf() :   returns the first index of a particular character.  
 
 
 
 more operation/methods o f string  @   "https://www.w3schools.com/java/java_ref_string.asp"
 
 
 
 Conctenation :  addition   
 
 +  is the concatenation operator on string 
 
 
 String s1 = "hello", s2 = "world";
 
 